To install libopenotp or your system:

Libopenotp requires libxml2 development library from http://xmlsoft.org/,
Zlib development library from from http://zlib.net/,
and openssl development library from http://www.openssl.org/.

1) Make sure you have libxml2 and openssl development libraries installed.
   On a RedHat / Centos system you can install the dependencies with:
   yum install libxml2-devel zlib-devel openssl-devel.
2) Compile libopenotp with 'make' command in the current directory.
3) Install libopenotp in /usr/lib/ or /usr/lib64/ with 'make install' command.

Alternativelly, you can use the precompiled library for Linux and Windows in build_xxx/
The precompiled libraries do not have any library dependencies.

1) Copy build_xxx/libopenotp.so* and libopenotp.a in /usr/lib/ or /usr/lib64/.
2) Copy build_xxx/openotp.h and build_xxx/opensso.h in /usr/include/.
